Wash and dry all produce. Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Rinse @lentils{1/2%cup}, then put in a #medium pot{} along with 1¼ cups water and a pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then lower heat and reduce to a simmer. Cook, uncovered, until tender, ~{20-30%minutes}.

Cut @radishes{3} and @Persian cucumber{1} in half lengthwise. Slice each into thin halfmoons. Peel @carrots{1}, then thinly slice on a diagonal. Pick fronds from @dill{1/4}(fronds picked and roughly chopped); discard stems. Cut @lemon{1} in half.

> Save one lemon half for dressing lentils and use other to season dressing and salad.

== Creamy Dill Dressing ==

In a #small bowl{}, stir together @sour cream{4%tablespoon}, half the dill, half the @Mediterranean spice blend{1%tablespoon}, a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tablespoon}, and a squeeze of lemon. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> Add a splash of water, if needed, to give dressing a drizzly consistency.

== Feta-Stuffed Pita ==

Cut @whole wheat pita{1} in half. Fill the pockets with remaining dill and half the @feta cheese{1%cup}(half for stuffing, half for garnish). Place on a #baking sheet{}. Bake in oven until feta cheese is soft and pita is lightly toasted, ~{6-8%minutes}.

== Salad ==

In a #large bowl{}, toss @arugula{2%ounce} with a squeeze of lemon, a drizzle of olive oil, and half the remaining Mediterranean spice. Season with salt and pepper.

Once lentils are done, remove from heat. Stir a drizzle of olive oil, juice of one lemon half, and remaining Mediterranean spice into pot. Season with salt and pepper.

Divide salad between plates. Top with lentils, radishes, cucumbers, and carrots. Sprinkle with remaining feta cheese. Drizzle with dressing. Serve with pita halves on the side.